pageContext.claim: “Bill was the only one that got it right, said, 'You don't wanna run against Trump. He said that very early.' He was the only one. He's the only one that understood what was going on, actually.”
pageContext.analysis: Former president Bill Clinton reportedly raised concerns that the campaign was failing to reach undecided voters such as working-class whites. But we couldn't find reports that Clinton specifically raised alarms about Michigan and Wisconsin, as Trump claimed.
